Typed semantic seed for 𝒢 (authoritative; DOT is presentation)
================================================================

Entity kinds (Node.kind):
  category_family      — e.g. Sets, Magmas, Rings, Modules(R)
  classifier_domain    — e.g. Sets.Finite as domain of ι_Finite
  derived_category     — named pullback / composite (not a new primitive)
  category_constructor — Arr(−), Slices, FunctorCategories, …
  alias                — synonym of another entity (not a distinct object)
  # Aut(L), Pic, OrthogonalGroups are NOT category_family nodes; see STATUS

Arrow kinds (Arrow.kind):
  forgetful
  full_inclusion
  classifier_leg          — ι_A : C.A → C
  pullback_projection     — a cone leg of a pullback presentation
  theorem_inclusion       — implication / theorem-witness inclusion
  equivalence
  construction            — associated / constructed functor (not supercategory)
  parameter_dependency    — parameter lives in a category (NOT object forgetful)

Optional authored arrow field:
  role — PortId / operation route (additive_operation | multiplicative_operation |
         underlying_set | …). Authored role wins over prose inference in the
         constructibility checker.

Classifier record fields:
  id, name, host_id, domain_id, leg_arrow_id
  transport: { along_functor_id, from_classifier_id } | null
  # Do NOT store property|structure|stuff — compute from the leg.

Derived definition (pullback):
  operation: pullback
  left: <forgetful or other functor id>
  right: <classifier_leg arrow id or classifier id>
  over: <base category id>
  strictness: strict | pseudo
  along: <optional PortId / operation route>
  notes: …

Derived definition (classifier tower / application):
  operation: classifier_tower | classifier_application
  base|host: <category id>
  classifiers|classifier: <classifier id(s)>
  along: <optional PortId / operation route>

Derived definition (parameter substitution):
  operation: parameter_substitution
  of: <category_family id>
  substitute: { param: expression }

Sage mapping: design/sage_to_normalized_map/correspondence.json
  sage_to_graph values are semantic_seed entity ids (target_kind).
  Presentation vertices are entity.dot_vertex (resolved in sage_to_stub).
